message:
Another excellent article in the series!

If a shutdown is already pending - due to `SIGINT` (CTRL+C) - then the finally block probably shouldn't attempt to stop the app again.

```cs
finally
{
  // only stop app if error occurred in this class
  if (!_hostApplicationLifetime.ApplicationStopping.IsCancellationRequested)
    _hostApplicationLifetime.StopApplication();
}
```

What do you think?
